BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Symphonic Band
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T200000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260503T213000Z
UID:d008890a15d4e5b75ff7dc1a2ba409e5@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Shawn Vondran\, conductor\nThe centerpiece of the Symphonic Ba
 nd’s first spring concert is Modest Mussorgsky’s Pictures at an Exhibi
 tion (orchestrated by Maurice Ravel and transcribed for band by Paul Laven
 der). The pictures the work depicts were created by Mussorgsky’s friend\
 , artist Viktor Hartmann. Following Hartmann’s untimely death\, the Impe
 rial Academy of Arts in Saint Petersburg exhibited his work\, and after to
 uring the exhibition\, Mussorgsky was inspired to compose the score.\nJoha
 n Halvorsen (arr. Frederick Fennell)\, Bojarernes intogsmarsch (Entry Marc
 h of the Boyars) \nEric Whitacre\, Lux Aurumque \nDennis Llinás\, La Ch
 ancla \nModest Mussorgsky (orch. Maurice Ravel\, trans. Paul Lavender)\, 
 Pictures at an Exhibition
LOCATION:Pick-Staiger Concert Hall\, 50 Arts Circle Drive\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://www.music.northwestern.edu/events/symphonic-band-9
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
