SUMMARY:Writers Fest 2026
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T220000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260512T230000Z
UID:c52f80a33823b3334b547bf5575cac11@northwestern.edu
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the 18th annual Writers Festival\, featurin
 g renowned writers offering public readings!\nThis year's featured writers
  are Leni Zumas\, Aminatta Forna\, and Marsha de la O. \nMay 11: Reading 
 by Leni Zumas at 5pm. \nLeni Zumas is the author of four books of fiction
 \, including Wolf Bells (Algonquin/Little\, Brown\, 2025). Her bestselling
  novel Red Clocks won the 2019 Oregon Book Award for Fiction and was short
 listed for the Orwell Prize for Political Fiction and the Neukom Award for
  Speculative Fiction.\nMay 12: Reading by Aminatta Forna at 5pm.\nAminatta
  Forna is the award-winning author of the novels Happiness\, The Hired Man
 \, The Memory of Love and Ancestor Stones\, and a memoir\, The Devil that 
 Danced on the Water. Her latest book\, an essay collection\, The Window Se
 at: Notes from a Life in Motion\, was published in 2021.\nMay 13: Reading 
 by Marsha de la O at 5pm. \nMarsha de la O was born and raised in Souther
 n California. She earned her MFA from Vermont College and is the author of
  two collections of poetry: Black Hope (1997)\, winner of the New Issues P
 oetry Prize\, and Antidote for Night (2015)\, winner of the Isabella Gardn
 er Prize from BOA Editions.
LOCATION:Deering Library\, 1937 Sheridan Road\, Evanston\, IL
URL:https://planitpurple.northwestern.edu/event/638527
X-SOURCE:Northwestern University
END:VEVENT
